cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY

This paper deals with bibliometric evaluation of authors based on coauthorship networks and citation counts. The paper uses a dataset from the CiteSeerX database, which is a digital library of computer science literature. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The paper also involves statistical analysis and regression, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also deals with citation analysis, which is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
